Hi Michael! Thanks for reporting this. Have you tried writing a file with only a subset of the columns to identify where the problem might be? 
When printing the schema with pyarrow, I see that some logical types are not recognized, could something be going wrong there?
 
{code}
  optional int64 field_id=13 ttl;
  optional int32 field_id=14 tripId (UNKNOWN);
  optional binary field_id=15 vin (String);
  optional binary field_id=16 state (String);
  optional int32 field_id=17 region (UNKNOWN);
  optional int64 field_id=18 outsideTemperature;
  optional int64 field_id=19 engineTemperature;
{code}

I added some debug output in the code and got some more details about the error:
{code}
ProtocolError {
    kind: InvalidData,
    message: "cannot convert enum constant 24 to ConvertedType",
}
{code}

The corresponding field name seems to be "tripId".

Seems to correspond to this type in the thrift definitions: https://github.com/apache/parquet-format/blob/master/src/main/thrift/parquet.thrift#L48
The enum values in that file only go to 21
